    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri Motors Safety Airways/193:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-10T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 10, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 10—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. A further despatch No. 183, February 3,<note n="45" xml:id="d34fn45">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning permission American Air Lines to traverse French
                    territory, leaves by pouch tomorrow. Since it was drafted, Ministry of Commerce
                    admits tenseness of situation and today informed Embassy it will shortly confer
                    with Minister for Foreign Affairs regarding possibility of some type of
                    temporary permission. Response on this latter point is expected end next
                    week.</p>
                <p>See also report of Military Attaché to War Department No. 15959 W, February
                    4.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
